  "texts": [
    "Since G/K is simply connected with non-positive curvature, the only way this can occur is if b 1 = b 2.",
    "Hence, we may identify B with its image, a totally geodesic submanifold of G/K.We claim that B ⊂ G/K is complete in the induced metric h * g sym.",
    "Indeed, let B = B0 × • • • × Br be the de Rham decomposition [KN63, Thm.",
    "IV.6.2] of B (for the metric g B), where B0 is a Euclidean space and the holonomy representation of ( Bi, g i) is irreducible for i > 0.",
    "(Here g i = gB | Bi.)"
